timedatectl is a command-line utility in Debian (and all systemd-based Linux systems) used to view and manage system time and date settings.

It allows you to:

    View the current system time, timezone, and NTP status
    Enable or disable automatic time synchronization (NTP)
    Change the systemâ€™s timezone or manually set the time

# install the package
sudo apt update
sudo apt install systemd-timesyncd

# enable and start the service
sudo systemctl enable systemd-timesyncd

sudo systemctl start systemd-timesyncd

# enable NTP sync via timedatectl
sudo timedatectl set-ntp true

# check the sync status
timedatectl status

Output:

Local time: Mon 2025-08-04 17:41:21 EEST
Universal time: Mon 2025-08-04 14:41:21 UTC
RTC time: Mon 2025-08-04 14:41:21
Time zone: Europe/Bucharest (EEST, +0300)
System clock synchronized: yes
NTP service: active
RTC in local TZ: no

# example of changing the time zone
sudo timedatectl set-timezone Europe/Paris
